{"sequence":52,"timestamp":"2026-04-29T23:14:16.231274274Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-438871e4","body":"`src/contexts/bead_workflow/project_prompt.rs:92` deserializes `br dep tree <id> --json` directly into `DepTreeNode`, and `src/contexts/bead_workflow/project_prompt.rs:186` then expects the direct dependencies under a nested `children` field. Current `br dep tree --json` emits a top-level flat array of tree nodes with `depth`/`parent_id` metadata, not a single nested object; see https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/beads_rust/blob/main/src/cli/commands/dep.rs#L988-L993. As a result, the real `BrAdapter` path will fail before rendering any prompt, while the tests only mock the incorrect nested shape. Add/adjust the dep-tree model to match the flat JSON output and derive direct blockers from depth/parent metadata, with an adapter-level test using the real flat shape.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"7ddade4e561e54efba1559a89d170b617cd04f8e35449b6cfcd9b906751037e8","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260429203958","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
